{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_7","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,220p' RULES.md\"","aggregated_output":"# MiniLang LSP server — required behavior\n\nComplete `src/server.mjs` so the MiniLang Language Server satisfies all of the following. The visible\ntests cover only part of this; implement the full spec.\n\n1. **JSON-RPC transport**: `encodeMessage` frames with `Content-Length` headers; `MessageBuffer.push`\n   parses streamed/split frames and returns complete messages.\n2. **Lifecycle**: `initialize` returns capabilities (textDocumentSync, completion, definition, hover);\n   `shutdown`/`exit` behave per LSP.\n3. **Diagnostics** (`didOpen`/`didChange` publish via `getDiagnostics`/notifications):\n   - undefined symbol references,\n   - wrong function arity (argument count mismatch),\n   - **syntax / brace recovery**: a malformed program (e.g. a missing `}`) still parses with error\n     recovery AND still reports the semantic diagnostics (undefined, arity) it can find.\n4. **didChange** updates the document incrementally and **clears stale diagnostics** that no longer apply.\n5. **Completion** filters by the current prefix and by scope, and exposes function signatures.\n6. **Go-to-definition** resolves to the correct symbol, preferring the **local scope** over a same-name\n   symbol elsewhere.\n7. **Hover** resolves function/symbol info.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_8","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"sed -n '1,320p' src/server.mjs\"","aggregated_output":"export function encodeMessage(message) {\n  const payload = JSON.stringify(message);\n  const length = Buffer.byteLength(payload, 'utf8');\n  return `Content-Length: ${length}\\r\\n\\r\\n${payload}`;\n}\n\nexport class MessageBuffer {\n  constructor() {\n    this.buffer = '';\n  }\n\n  push(chunk) {\n    this.buffer += chunk;\n    const messages = [];\n\n    while (true) {\n      const headerEnd = this.buffer.indexOf('\\r\\n\\r\\n');\n      if (headerEnd === -1) {\n        break;\n      }\n\n      const header = this.buffer.slice(0, headerEnd);\n      const contentLengthLine = header\n        .split('\\r\\n')\n        .find((line) => /^content-length:/i.test(line));\n      if (!contentLengthLine) {\n        throw new Error('Invalid JSON-RPC framing: missing Content-Length');\n      }\n\n      const contentLength = Number(contentLengthLine.split(':')[1]?.trim());\n      if (!Number.isFinite(contentLength) || contentLength < 0) {\n        throw new Error('Invalid JSON-RPC framing: invalid Content-Length');\n      }\n\n      const bodyStart = headerEnd + 4;\n      const bodyEnd = bodyStart + contentLength;\n      if (this.buffer.length < bodyEnd) {\n        break;\n      }\n\n      const body = this.buffer.slice(bodyStart, bodyEnd);\n      this.buffer = this.buffer.slice(bodyEnd);\n      messages.push(JSON.parse(body));\n    }\n\n    return messages;\n  }\n}\n\nconst KEYWORDS = new Set(['fn', 'let', 'return']);\n\nfunction parseParams(paramText) {\n  return paramText\n    .split(',')\n    .map((item) => item.trim())\n    .filter(Boolean);\n}\n\nfunction makeRange(lineText, line, start, name) {\n  return {\n    start: { line, character: start },\n    end: { line, character: start + name.length }\n  };\n}\n\nfunction makeDiagnostic(lineText, line, match, message) {\n  return {\n    message,\n    severity: 1,\n    range: {\n      start: { line, character: match.index },\n      end: { line, character: match.index + match[0].length }\n    }\n  };\n}\n\nfunction symbolKey(line, from, to) {\n  return `${line}:${from}-${to}`;\n}\n\nfunction countCallArgs(lineText, openIndex) {\n  let depth = 0;\n  let closeIndex = -1;\n\n  for (let i = openIndex; i < lineText.length; i += 1) {\n    const char = lineText[i];\n    if (char === '(') {\n      depth += 1;\n    } else if (char === ')') {\n      depth -= 1;\n      if (depth === 0) {\n        closeIndex = i;\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (closeIndex === -1) {\n    return { count: null, closeIndex };\n  }\n\n  const argsText = lineText.slice(openIndex + 1, closeIndex).trim();\n  if (!argsText) {\n    return { count: 0, closeIndex };\n  }\n\n  let nested = 0;\n  let count = 1;\n  for (const char of argsText) {\n    if (char === '(') {\n      nested += 1;\n    } else if (char === ')') {\n      nested -= 1;\n    } else if (char === ',' && nested === 0) {\n      count += 1;\n    }\n  }\n\n  return { count, closeIndex };\n}\n\nfunction tokenAt(lineText, column) {\n  if (!lineText) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  if (!/[A-Za-z_]/.test(lineText[column] || '')) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  let start = column;\n  while (start > 0 && /[A-Za-z0-9_]/.test(lineText[start - 1])) {\n    start -= 1;\n  }\n\n  let end = column;\n  while (end < lineText.length && /[A-Za-z0-9_]/.test(lineText[end])) {\n    end += 1;\n  }\n\n  if (start === end) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  return {\n    name: lineText.slice(start, end),\n    start,\n    end\n  };\n}\n\nexport function parseMiniLang(text) {\n  const lines = text.split('\\n');\n  const diagnostics = [];\n  const symbols = [];\n  const declarationTokens = new Set();\n  const scopes = [\n    {\n      id: 'global',\n      startLine: 0,\n      endLine: Infinity,\n      depth: 0,\n      symbols: new Map()\n    }\n  ];\n  const activeScopes = [scopes[0]];\n\n  let depth = 0;\n\n  for (let line = 0; line < lines.length; line += 1) {\n    const lineText = lines[line];\n\n    const fnMatch = lineText.match(/^\\s*fn\\s+([A-Za-z_]\\w*)\\s*\\(([^)]*)\\)\\s*(\\{)?/);\n    const currentScope = activeScopes[activeScopes.length - 1];\n\n    if (fnMatch) {\n      const name = fnMatch[1];\n      const params = parseParams(fnMatch[2] || '');\n      const nameIndex = lineText.indexOf(name);\n      const fnSymbol = {\n        kind: 'function',\n        name,\n        range: makeRange(lineText, line, nameIndex, name),\n        params,\n        scopeId: `fn:${name}:${line}`,\n        declLine: line\n      };\n      currentScope.symbols.set(name, fnSymbol);\n      symbols.push(fnSymbol);\n      declarationTokens.add(symbolKey(line, nameIndex, nameIndex + name.length));\n\n      const functionScope = {\n        id: fnSymbol.scopeId,\n        startLine: line,\n        endLine: Infinity,\n        depth: depth + 1,\n        symbols: new Map()\n      };\n      scopes.push(functionScope);\n      activeScopes.push(functionScope);\n\n      let searchFrom = fnMatch[0].indexOf('(') + 1;\n      for (const param of params) {\n        const paramIndex = lineText.indexOf(param, searchFrom);\n        if (paramIndex !== -1) {\n          const paramSymbol = {\n            kind: 'variable',\n            name: param,\n            range: makeRange(lineText, line, paramIndex, param),\n            declLine: line,\n            scopeId: functionScope.id\n          };\n          functionScope.symbols.set(param, paramSymbol);\n          symbols.push(paramSymbol);\n          declarationTokens.add(symbolKey(line, paramIndex, paramIndex + param.length));\n          searchFrom = paramIndex + param.length;\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    const letMatch = lineText.match(/^\\s*let\\s+([A-Za-z_]\\w*)\\s*=/);\n    const activeScope = activeScopes[activeScopes.length - 1];\n    if (letMatch) {\n      const name = letMatch[1];\n      const nameIndex = lineText.indexOf(name);\n      const localSymbol = {\n        kind: 'variable',\n        name,\n        range: makeRange(lineText, line, nameIndex, name),\n        declLine: line,\n        scopeId: activeScope.id\n      };\n      activeScope.symbols.set(name, localSymbol);\n      symbols.push(localSymbol);\n      declarationTokens.add(symbolKey(line, nameIndex, nameIndex + name.length));\n    }\n\n    const identifierRE = /[A-Za-z_]\\w*/g;\n    const tokenCandidates = [...lineText.matchAll(identifierRE)];\n\n    for (const match of tokenCandidates) {\n      const token = match[0];\n      const index = match.index;\n\n      if (KEYWORDS.has(token)) {\n        continue;\n      }\n\n      const tokenStart = index;\n      const tokenEnd = index + token.length;\n      if (declarationTokens.has(symbolKey(line, tokenStart, tokenEnd))) {\n        continue;\n      }\n\n      const after = lineText.slice(tokenEnd);\n      const hasCall = /^\\s*\\(/.test(after);\n      const whitespace = /^\\s*/.exec(after)[0].length;\n      const openParenIndex = tokenEnd + whitespace;\n\n      let found = null;\n      for (let i = activeScopes.length - 1; i >= 0; i -= 1) {\n        if (activeScopes[i].symbols.has(token)) {\n          found = activeScopes[i].symbols.get(token);\n          break;\n        }\n      }\n\n      if (hasCall) {\n        const { count } = countCallArgs(lineText, openParenIndex);\n        if (count === null) {\n          continue;\n        }\n\n        if (!found || found.kind !== 'function') {\n          diagnostics.push(\n            makeDiagnostic(\n              lineText,\n              line,\n              match,\n              `Undefined symbol '${token}'`\n            )\n          );\n          continue;\n        }\n\n        if (count !== found.params.length) {\n          diagnostics.push(\n            makeDiagnostic(\n              lineText,\n              line,\n              match,\n              `Function '${token}' expects ${found.params.length} arguments but got ${count}`\n            )\n          );\n        }\n\n        continue;\n      }\n\n      if (!found) {\n        diagnostics.push(\n          makeDiagnostic(\n            lineText,\n            line,\n            match,\n            `Undefined symbol '${token}'`\n          )\n        );\n      }\n    }\n\n    const openCount = (lineText.match(/\\{/g) || []).length;\n    const closeCount = (lineText.match(/\\}/g) || []).length;\n    const nextDepth = depth + openCount - closeCount;\n    depth = nextDepth;\n\n    while (activeScopes.length > 1 && activeScopes[activeScopes.length - 1].depth > depth) {\n      const finishedScope = activeScopes.pop();\n      finishedScope.endLine = line;\n    }\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
