{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_22","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/zsh -lc \"awk '{print NR \\\":\\\" \"'$0}'\"' RULES.md | sed -n '1,80p'\"","aggregated_output":"1:# MiniLang LSP server — required behavior\n2:\n3:Complete `src/server.mjs` so the MiniLang Language Server satisfies all of the following. The visible\n4:tests cover only part of this; implement the full spec.\n5:\n6:1. **JSON-RPC transport**: `encodeMessage` frames with `Content-Length` headers; `MessageBuffer.push`\n7:   parses streamed/split frames and returns complete messages.\n8:2. **Lifecycle**: `initialize` returns capabilities (textDocumentSync, completion, definition, hover);\n9:   `shutdown`/`exit` behave per LSP.\n10:3. **Diagnostics** (`didOpen`/`didChange` publish via `getDiagnostics`/notifications):\n11:   - undefined symbol references,\n12:   - wrong function arity (argument count mismatch),\n13:   - **syntax / brace recovery**: a malformed program (e.g. a missing `}`) still parses with error\n14:     recovery AND still reports the semantic diagnostics (undefined, arity) it can find.\n15:4. **didChange** updates the document incrementally and **clears stale diagnostics** that no longer apply.\n16:5. **Completion** filters by the current prefix and by scope, and exposes function signatures.\n17:6. **Go-to-definition** resolves to the correct symbol, preferring the **local scope** over a same-name\n18:   symbol elsewhere.\n19:7. **Hover** resolves function/symbol info.\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
